Mexico Stocks: Compartamos, Grupo Mexico Gain; OHL Mexico Falls

-- B y   K a t i a   P o r z e c a n s k i
-- 
2011-12-02T16:52:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/mexico-stocks-compartamos-grupo-mexico-gain-ohl-mexico-falls.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:35 a.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  rose 0.7 percent to 36,839.42.  Mexican stocks rose after the U.S. unemployment rate
unexpectedly dropped in November to a two-year low of 8.6
percent from 9 percent, Labor Department figures showed today in
Washington, and Mexico’s central bank left the benchmark lending
rate unchanged at 4.5 percent.  Consorcio Ara SAB (ARA*)  , a Mexican homebuilder,
advanced 3 percent to 3.79 pesos.  Compartamos SAB  (COMPARC* MM),
the holding company that controls microlender Banco Compartamos,
rose 3.1 percent to 18.74 pesos.  Grupo Comercial Chedraui SA (CHDRAUIB) 
, the supermarket chain based in Xalapa, Mexico,
increased 1.7 percent to 32.80 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, rose 2.2 percent to 37 pesos. Copper futures for
March delivery gained 1.3 percent in  New York , heading for the
first weekly gain in five weeks.  OHL Mexico SAB (OHLMEX*)  , the Mexican unit of Spanish
construction company Obrascon Huarte Lain SA, fell 0.9 percent
to 22.42 pesos. Telefonos de Mexico, a unit of  America Movil 
SAB, said in an e-mailed statement yesterday that it filed a
complaint with authorities against OHL after the company cut two
fiber-optic lines owned by America Movil in Mexico City.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Porzecanski in New York at 
 kporzecansk1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
